info.name: Intermediolateral cell column
info.description: The intermediolateral cell column of the spinal cord is AKA the lateral horn of spinal cord. It is a small, pointed, lateral extension of the gray matter from T1 through L2 or L3 that is composed of preganglionic sympathetic neurons.
info.item: /Sections/Thin, Spinal Cord to Cerebrum/3 Lumbar cord, upper
